</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7A475BD2766D5DDCC3663562F9E7DEA3" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="57257E82D9D3113A9C8A24996155C9D8" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6447AAD26706339BD46DC44D57C16A27" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
<taxonomicName id="40F31D1F56B8B042EC309FC82544D9A0" authorityName="Wierzbicka, Pielich. &amp; Wasowicz" authorityYear="2020" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Biscutella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Biscutella laevigata subsp. woycickii" order="Brassicales" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="laevigata" subSpecies="woycickii">Biscutella laevigata subsp. woycickii</taxonomicName>
is similar to subsp. 
<taxonomicName id="D622A1D8F2F2936C11A1560A84B0D190" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Biscutella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="subsp. gracilis" order="Brassicales" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="laevigata" subSpecies="gracilis">gracilis</taxonomicName>
, but differs from the latter in having thin, light-green rosette leaves very densely covered by simple non-glandular trichomes. Plants belonging to subsp. 
<taxonomicName id="C82CB3F921F453318F2EDA31582C5E79" authorityName="Wierzbicka, Pielich. &amp; Wasowicz" authorityYear="2020" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Biscutella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="subsp. woycickii" order="Brassicales" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="laevigata" subSpecies="woycickii">woycickii</taxonomicName>
have smaller seeds and are characterised by the ability to tolerate and accumulate high quantities of heavy metals.
</paragraph>
<caption id="BA2EE16D35AB4540763D8D371E9EF299" doi="10.3897/phytokeys.160.53937.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/450549" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" start="Figure 1" startId="F1">
<paragraph id="81D879FAB457855750B4BB86224B4DB8" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
<emphasis id="F2AFBC00B774535B60560C9C548FD82D" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Figure 1.</emphasis>
A holotype of 
<taxonomicName id="0A5A595032998F5938ADF2D536184C51" authorityName="Wierzbicka, Pielich. &amp; Wasowicz" authorityYear="2020" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Biscutella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Biscutella laevigata subsp. woycickii" order="Brassicales" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="laevigata" subSpecies="woycickii">Biscutella laevigata subsp. woycickii</taxonomicName>
Wierzbicka, Pielichowska &amp; Wasowicz (WA0000071422).
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="03E55F3AF70EB990D76A04F2692138AD" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="108E355CE1238BCF697C5C687625886C" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7199AB72A096794A43BAC4DCE9A59127" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
This subspecies is dedicated to a renowned Polish botanist Zygmunt 
<normalizedToken id="D4CA4A5ABABB9A7223EEF1BC6775459E" originalValue="Wóycicki">Woycicki</normalizedToken>
(1871-1941), a pioneer of biological research on calamine areas.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="CAA0EA182810BC66BDC0FAFD6AE8D95D" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="57835BE425678BA0DA639624359E120E" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Distribution and ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D34DBF605D4416697213DEE5FE50C193" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
Calamine areas in the vicinity of Olkusz, Powiat Olkuski (Olkusz County), 
<normalizedToken id="5AA9F2AFF9D9F8A0598FA650ACC37CEE" originalValue="Województwo">Wojewodztwo</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="8B20C458243800FBD93D7E1303FCB749" originalValue="Małopolskie">Malopolskie</normalizedToken>
(Lesser Poland Voivodeship/Province), southern Poland.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9C945038CE65360BA2F5A68A8B183C74" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="phenology">
<paragraph id="CAD3A8CAF77290C9A15F6934E7AB1415" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Phenology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="08AA38855468BAB7E7B6B3BC39EE844B" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Flowering in April-May, fruiting in July-August.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="EF028EBCEB1E1507F0D21D97E2A7B23A" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="chromosome number">
<paragraph id="4D7044D9886AC9C31C622642C3F8C019" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Chromosome number.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4467061921DC47251902ED073DB9D2A7" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
A study carried out by 
<bibRefCitation id="560B0E3DAA200B1D33EF0925ADE3267F" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5586/asbp.1950.003" author="Skalinska, M" journalOrPublisher="Acta Societatis Botanicorum Poloniae" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="45 - 68" refId="B6" refString="Skalinska, M, 1950. Studies in chromosome numbers of Polish Angiosperms. Acta Societatis Botanicorum Poloniae 20 (1): 45 - 68, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5586/asbp.1950.003" title="Studies in chromosome numbers of Polish Angiosperms." url="https://doi.org/10.5586/asbp.1950.003" volume="20" year="1950">
<normalizedToken id="F8C6173139795C3204CEB0BDC37D188A" originalValue="Skalińska">Skalinska</normalizedToken>
(1950)
</bibRefCitation>
on plants from the calamine population in the vicinity of Olkusz resulted in the diploid chromosome number, 2 
<emphasis id="9AB87BD6887A64A53A92BF9F099F3C98" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">n</emphasis>
= 18.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="168AFE22CDF10DEE2E51734671A8F68D" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="preliminary conservation status">
<paragraph id="C584B98A350C279FE75972B67B12348A" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Preliminary conservation status.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5417B94FF3532A96E74C376B43AF27F3" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Currently, the taxon is known only from calamine areas in the vicinity of Olkusz, where it is quite abundant on calamine soils. The extent of occurrence (EOO) of the taxon is 7 km2 and the area of occupancy (AOO) is 14 km2. A steady decline in population size has been observed during the last 20 years. It seems that the new taxon could be classified as Vulnerable according to the IUCN criteria (Standards IUCN 2019), but more research is needed to estimate the number of mature individuals and population dynamics.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
